llm_answer:
For a reversible phase change carried out at the temperature of the surroundings (here, the normal boiling point), the entropy change of the surroundings is  

\[
\Delta S_{\text{sur}} = -\frac{q_{\text{rev}}}{T_{\text{sur}}}
                      = -\frac{\Delta H_{\text{vap}}}{T_{\text{b}}}
\]

Given  
ΔH₍vap₎ = 29.4 kJ mol⁻¹ = 2.94 × 10⁴ J mol⁻¹  
T_b = 334.88 K  

\[
\Delta S_{\text{sur}} = -\frac{2.94 \times 10^{4}\ \text{J mol}^{-1}}{334.88\ \text{K}}
                      = -87.8\ \text{J K}^{-1}\text{ mol}^{-1}
\]

\[
\boxed{-87.8} \text{ J K}^{-1}\text{ mol}^{-1}
\]

