llm_answer:
For 1 mol of an ideal gas  

V_{ideal}= \dfrac{RT}{P}

Given that the actual molar volume is 12 % smaller than this value,

V_{real}= V_{ideal}(1-0.12)=0.88\,V_{ideal}

The compression (compressibility) factor Z is

Z=\dfrac{P\,V_{real}}{RT}= \dfrac{V_{real}}{V_{ideal}}=0.88

\boxed{0.88}

