llm_answer:
Photon energy  
\[
E_{h\nu}= \frac{hc}{\lambda}
          =\frac{(6.626\times10^{-34}\,\text{J\,s})(2.998\times10^{8}\,\text{m\,s}^{-1})}
                 {58.4\times10^{-9}\,\text{m}}
          =3.40\times10^{-18}\,\text{J}
\]

Kinetic energy of the ejected electron  
\[
E_{\text{kin}}=\frac{1}{2}m_{e}v^{2}
              =\tfrac12(9.109\times10^{-31}\,\text{kg})(1.59\times10^{6}\,\text{m\,s}^{-1})^{2}
              =1.15\times10^{-18}\,\text{J}
\]

Ionization energy (work function)  
\[
E_{\text{ion}} = E_{h\nu}-E_{\text{kin}}
               =(3.40-1.15)\times10^{-18}\,\text{J}
               =2.25\times10^{-18}\,\text{J}
\]

Conversion to electron-volts  
\[
E_{\text{ion}}=\frac{2.25\times10^{-18}\,\text{J}}{1\,\text{eV}/(1.602\times10^{-19}\,\text{J})}
              =1.41\times10^{1}\,\text{eV}\approx14.1\,\text{eV}
\]

\[
\boxed{14.1} \text{ eV}
\]

