Let  

c_{\mathrm{Co}},\;c_{\mathrm{Ni}} = molar concentrations (mol L^{-1}) of the Co– and Ni–dithiol complexes in the final 50.0 mL solution that is placed in the 1.00-cm cell.

1.  Solve the simultaneous Beer–Lambert equations  

\[
\begin{aligned}
A_{510} &= \varepsilon_{\mathrm{Co},510}\,c_{\mathrm{Co}}+\varepsilon_{\mathrm{Ni},510}\,c_{\mathrm{Ni}}
         =36400\,c_{\mathrm{Co}}+5520\,c_{\mathrm{Ni}}=0.446 \\[4pt]
A_{656} &= \varepsilon_{\mathrm{Co},656}\,c_{\mathrm{Co}}+\varepsilon_{\mathrm{Ni},656}\,c_{\mathrm{Ni}}
         =1240\,c_{\mathrm{Co}}+17500\,c_{\mathrm{Ni}}=0.326
\end{aligned}
\]

(using b = 1.00 cm).

Determinant  

\[
\Delta = (36400)(17500)-(5520)(1240)=6.301552\times10^{8}
\]

\[
\begin{aligned}
c_{\mathrm{Ni}} &=\frac{36400(0.326)-1240(0.446)}{\Delta}
                =\frac{1.131336\times10^{4}}{6.301552\times10^{8}}
                =1.795\times10^{-5}\;\text{mol\,L}^{-1} \\[6pt]
c_{\mathrm{Co}} &=\frac{17500(0.446)-5520(0.326)}{\Delta}
                =9.54\times10^{-6}\;\text{mol\,L}^{-1}
\end{aligned}
\]

2.  Relation between the analysed solution and the original sample  

• Original digest volume = 50.0 mL.  
• 25.0 mL aliquot (½ of digest) diluted to 50.0 mL for measurement (×½ dilution).  

Hence the concentration in the digest is twice that in the measurement solution, and the total moles of Ni originating from the whole sample are  

\[
n_{\mathrm{Ni}} = (2c_{\mathrm{Ni}})(0.0500\;\text{L}) 
                = 0.100\,c_{\mathrm{Ni}}
                = 0.100(1.795\times10^{-5})
                = 1.80\times10^{-6}\;\text{mol}
\]

3.  Mass of Ni in the sample  

\[
m_{\mathrm{Ni}} = n_{\mathrm{Ni}}\,M_{\mathrm{Ni}}
                =(1.80\times10^{-6}\;\text{mol})(58.69\;\text{g mol}^{-1})
                =1.05\times10^{-4}\;\text{g}=0.105\;\text{mg}
\]

4.  Parts per million of Ni in the 0.425 g sample  

\[
\text{ppm Ni}= \frac{m_{\mathrm{Ni}}\;(\text{mg})}{m_{\text{sample}}\;(\text{kg})}
             =\frac{0.105\;\text{mg}}{0.000425\;\text{kg}}
             =2.48\times10^{2}
\]

\[
\boxed{2.48\times10^{2}} \; \text{Ni(ppm)}
\]

