The titration determines how many carboxylic‐acid end groups are present; each neutralised group corresponds to one polymer molecule.  
(1) Moles of \(\ce{KOH}\) used  
\[
n_{\ce{KOH}} = C\,V = (0.0400\ \mathrm{mol\,dm^{-3}})(6.81\times10^{-3}\ \mathrm{dm^{3}})
              = 2.724\times10^{-4}\ \mathrm{mol}
\]

(2) Stoichiometry  
\[
\ce{PLA{-}COOH + KOH -> PLA{-}COOK + H2O}
\]
1 mol \(\ce{KOH}\) neutralises 1 mol carboxyl end groups  ⇒ \(n_{\text{chains}} = n_{\ce{KOH}}\).

(3) Number‐average molar mass  
\[
M_n = \frac{m_{\text{sample}}}{n_{\text{chains}}}
     = \frac{0.1619\ \mathrm{g}}{2.724\times10^{-4}\ \mathrm{mol}}
     = 5.94\times10^{2}\ \mathrm{g\,mol^{-1}}
\]

\[
\boxed{5.94\times10^{2}}\ \mathrm{g\ mol^{-1}}
\]

